            <h2>Diagnostic Reasoning in Hospital Medicine</h2>
            <div class="content-section" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                <h3>Case: 82-Year-Old Male with Recurrent Pneumonia</h3>
                <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-top: 20px;">
                    A teaching case demonstrating comprehensive chart review, diagnostic reasoning, and care coordination
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="learning-point" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                <h3>Learning Objectives</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Develop systematic approaches to comprehensive chart review</li>
                    <li>Recognize infection risk in chronic lymphoproliferative disorders</li>
                    <li>Apply clinical reasoning when laboratory and clinical findings diverge</li>
                    <li>Implement antibiotic stewardship principles</li>
                    <li>Identify opportunities for quality improvement</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <p style="font-size: 1.1em;"><strong>Note:</strong> Real de-identified case. Focus on learning and systems improvement.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SLIDE 2 -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>Initial Presentation</h1>
