            <div class="content-section" style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <h3>Additional Findings</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Troponin:</strong> 27 → 31 → 32 (stable)</li>
                    <li><strong>BNP:</strong> 3,743 (markedly elevated)</li>
                    <li><strong>Procalcitonin:</strong> 0.07 (very low)</li>
                    <li><strong>Viral panel:</strong> Negative (Flu, RSV, COVID)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <p><strong>Pattern:</strong> Leukocytosis, chronic anemia, very low procalcitonin. What does this suggest?</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SLIDE 4 -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>The Pivotal CT Scan</h1>
            <div class="success-box">
                <h3>Finding #1: No PE</h3>
                <p><span class="checkmark">✓</span> No acute pulmonary embolism</p>
            </div>
            <div class="content-section">
                <h3>Finding #2: Pulmonary Parenchyma</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>RLL consolidation</li>
                    <li>Scattered bilateral ground-glass opacities</li>
                    <li>Pattern: Pneumonia ± aspiration</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="critical-box">
                <h3>Finding #3: Critical Observation</h3>
                <blockquote style="font-size: 1.2em; background: white;">
                    "Constellation of findings suggestive of <strong>lymphomatous disorder</strong> with
                    multiple areas of <strong>lymphadenopathy</strong> in chest and upper abdomen"
                </blockquote>
                <h4 style="margin-top: 20px;">Lymphadenopathy:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Axillary (bilateral)</li>
                    <li>Mediastinal (multiple)</li>
                    <li>Hilar (bilateral)</li>
                    <li>Retroperitoneal, Porta hepatis</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold;">
                    <span class="lab-high">GENERALIZED LYMPHADENOPATHY</span>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="emphasis">
                The radiologist is telling us: lymphoproliferative disorder
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SLIDE 5 -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>Learning Opportunity: What Was in the Chart</h1>
            <div class="critical-box">
                <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Hematology Note - 3 Months Prior</h2>
                <p style="font-size: 1.2em;">Comprehensive note from <strong>August 2025</strong> (11 weeks before admission)</p>
            </div>
            <div class="content-section">
                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <h4>Established Diagnosis</h4>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.3em; font-weight: bold; color: var(--accent-color);">
                        Small Lymphocytic Lymphoma/Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia (SLL/CLL)
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Diagnosed:</strong> July 2024 (16 months prior)</li>
                        <li><strong>Stage:</strong> Lugano Stage III</li>
                        <li><strong>Treatment:</strong> Active surveillance</li>
                        <li><strong>Last visit:</strong> August 2025 (3 months ago)</li>
                        <li><strong>Due for follow-up:</strong> November 2025 (when admitted!)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <h4>Diagnostic Workup</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Flow cytometry: 90% clonal B-cells (CD19+CD5+CD23+)</li>
                    <li>PET CT: Stage III disease</li>
                    <li>FISH: ATM deletion, 13q14.2</li>
                    <li>IGVH: Non-mutated</li>
                </ul>
                <h4>Clinical Status (August)</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Feeling well, independent in ADLs</li>
                    <li>Active, driving, managing properties</li>
                    <li>Physical exam: 2cm cervical node palpable</li>
                    <li>Labs: WBC 7.34, ALC 3.48</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="success-box">
                <p><strong>Follow-up plan:</strong> "Return in 3 months" - due November 2025</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SLIDE 6 -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>Flow Cytometry Results (Diagnostic)</h1>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h4>90% clonal B-cells</h4>
            </div>
            <table>
                <thead><tr><th>Marker</th><th>Result</th><th>Significance</th></tr></thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>CD19</td><td class="checkmark">+</td><td>B-cell marker</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>CD5</td><td class="checkmark">+</td><td>Abnormal for B-cells</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>CD23</td><td class="checkmark">Partial</td><td>Typical for CLL</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Surface Ig</td><td>Dim lambda</td><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>CD10</td><td class="crossmark">-</td><td>Rules out follicular</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Kappa:Lambda</td><td class="lab-high">0.01</td><td>Restricted (nl ~2:1)</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <div class="critical-box" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <h3>Interpretation</h3>
                <p style="font-size: 1.3em; font-weight: bold;">
                    This immunophenotype is DIAGNOSTIC for CLL/SLL
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="learning-point">
                <h3>IWCLL 2018 Diagnostic Criteria</h3>
                <p><strong>CLL requires:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>≥5,000/µL clonal B-lymphocytes × 3 months, OR</li>
                    <li>ANY count with lymphadenopathy/organomegaly</li>
                    <li>PLUS characteristic flow cytometry</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SLIDE 7 -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>Hospital Course: Days 2-3</h1>
            <div class="timeline">
                <div class="timeline-item" style="background: #d4edda;">
                    <div class="timeline-date">Day 2 - Clinical Improvement</div>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> <strong>Weaned to room air</strong></li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> Afebrile throughout</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> Hemodynamically stable</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> No symptoms</li>
                        <li><strong>Echo:</strong> EF 60-65%, no vegetation</li>
                        <li><strong>Troponin:</strong> Flat - demand ischemia</li>
                        <li><strong>Creatinine:</strong> 2.60 → 2.31 (improving)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Antibiotics:</strong> Ceftriaxone + Azithromycin (Day 1/5)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item" style="background: #fff3cd;">
                    <div class="timeline-date">Day 3 - WBC Change</div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Patient wants to go home</li>
                        <li>SpO2 95% on room air</li>
                        <li>Afebrile, stable</li>
                        <li><strong>WBC: 13.61 → 14.98</strong> (↑10%)</li>
                        <li>Hemoglobin: 10.8 → 9.9</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Decision:</strong> Discontinued ceftriaxone + azithromycin, started Zosyn</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SLIDE 8 -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>Clinical Reasoning Question</h1>
            <div class="learning-point">
                <h3>When Lab and Clinical Picture Diverge</h3>
                <p style="font-size: 1.1em;">Day 3: WBC ↑ but patient clinically improved. Escalate antibiotics?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="two-column">
                <div class="content-section">
                    <h4>Clinical Picture</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> Weaned to room air</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> Afebrile × 72 hours</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> Stable vitals</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> No distress</li>
                        <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> Creatinine improving</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>IDSA:</strong> Clinical stability = success</p>
                </div>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <h4>Laboratory</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="warning">!</span> WBC 13.61 → 14.98</li>
                        <li>No differential ordered</li>
                        <li>Blood cultures negative</li>
                        <li>Procalcitonin was 0.07</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="critical-box" style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <h3>Understanding WBC in CLL</h3>
                <p><strong>If CLL diagnosis known:</strong> WBC elevation represents baseline lymphocytosis, NOT treatment failure</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>From August labs:</strong> ALC was 3.48 K/µL (elevated baseline)</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Should have:</strong> Ordered CBC differential to distinguish lymphocytes (CLL) from neutrophils (infection)</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <p><strong>Teaching Point:</strong> Total WBC alone insufficient. Always check differential.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SLIDE 9 -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>Teaching: Systematic Chart Review</h1>
            <div class="learning-point">
                <h3>The SEARCH Mnemonic</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="content-section">
                <p><strong>S</strong>EARCH systematically: Use EMR keywords ("biopsy," "flow cytometry," "hematology")</p>
                <p><strong>E</strong>XAMINE problem list: Active AND inactive diagnoses</p>
                <p><strong>A</strong>SK specific questions: "Ever had lymph node biopsy?" "See cancer doctor?"</p>
                <p><strong>R</strong>EVIEW prior imaging: NEW vs CHRONIC changes management</p>
                <p><strong>C</strong>HECK medications: Prophylactic antibiotics? Chemotherapy? Iron?</p>
                <p><strong>H</strong>OSPITAL/specialty records: Pathology, discharge summaries, subspecialty notes</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <h3>This Case</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Hematology note from 3 months ago: RIGHT THERE</li>
                    <li>Flow cytometry report: IN THE CHART</li>
                    <li>Prior imaging: DOCUMENTED</li>
                    <li>Follow-up plan: CLEARLY STATED</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top: 15px; font-weight: bold;">Critical information was available - needed systematic search</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- SLIDE 10 -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h1>Key Takeaways</h1>
            <div class="learning-point">
                <h3>1. Comprehensive Chart Review</h3>
                <p>Use systematic approach (SEARCH). Critical information usually in chart.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="learning-point">
                <h3>2. CLL = Immunocompromised</h3>
                <p>Infection leading cause of morbidity. Check IgG levels, consider prophylaxis, coordinate with hematology.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="learning-point">
                <h3>3. Clinical Picture > Labs</h3>
                <p>IDSA: Clinical stability = success. WBC normalization not required. Always check differential.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="learning-point">
                <h3>4. Stewardship in Complex Patients</h3>
                <p>Appropriate empiric therapy. Avoid unnecessary escalation in improving patients. 5-7 days sufficient for CAP.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="learning-point">
                <h3>5. Care Coordination</h3>
                <p>Contact established subspecialists. Patient missed hematology appointment due to hospitalization.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="emphasis" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                Focus on learning and systems improvement
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="nav-controls">
        <button class="nav-btn" id="prevBtn" onclick="changeSlide(-1)">← Previous</button>
        <button class="nav-btn" id="nextBtn" onclick="changeSlide(1)">Next →</button>
    </div>

    <script>
        let currentSlide = 0;
        const slides = document.querySelectorAll('.slide');
        const totalSlides = slides.length;
        document.getElementById('total-slides').textContent = totalSlides;

        function showSlide(n) {
            slides[currentSlide].classList.remove('active');
            currentSlide = (n + totalSlides) % totalSlides;
            slides[currentSlide].classList.add('active');
            document.getElementById('current-slide').textContent = currentSlide + 1;
            document.getElementById('prevBtn').disabled = currentSlide === 0;
            document.getElementById('nextBtn').disabled = currentSlide === totalSlides - 1;
            slides[currentSlide].scrollTop = 0;
        }

        function changeSlide(direction) {
            showSlide(currentSlide + direction);
        }

        document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
            if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') changeSlide(-1);
            if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') changeSlide(1);
        });

        let touchStartX = 0;
        let touchEndX = 0;
        document.addEventListener('touchstart', (e) => { touchStartX = e.changedTouches[0].screenX; });
        document.addEventListener('touchend', (e) => {
            touchEndX = e.changedTouches[0].screenX;
            const swipeThreshold = 50;
            if (touchEndX < touchStartX - swipeThreshold) changeSlide(1);
            if (touchEndX > touchStartX + swipeThreshold) changeSlide(-1);
        });

        showSlide(0);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
